race.comment: GOING NUCLEAR (3) goes well for hoop Kendal who has four wins and a placing from just six rides and again gets the benefit of her 1.5kg claim. Has only missed a drum once in nine spins around this circuit and looks very hard to toss. DIVINE PURPOSE (4) has been right there in both runs this campaign and looks ready for the mile journey now. Has the ability to take this out. The well-related PEROVIC (6) (half to 2xG1 winner King's Legacy) went down by the narrowest of margins last time out and is usually thereabouts. Top-three commodity. HYDE PARK (12) will appreciate the sharp drop in weight and looks one for the exotics players. ACROPHOBIC (1) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
